### Gym Booking System — Manual API Tests
### Requires: VS Code REST Client extension
### Start server: python manage.py runserver

@base = http://127.0.0.1:8000/api
@adminUser = admin
@adminPass = admin123
@testUser = testuser1
@testPass = TestPass123!

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. AUTH
# ─────────────────────────────────────────

### 1.1 Register a new user
POST {{base}}/auth/register/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser1",
  "email": "testuser1@example.com",
  "password": "TestPass123!"
}

###

### 1.2 Login as regular user → copy access token to @userToken below
POST {{base}}/auth/login/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser1",
  "password": "TestPass123!"
}

###

### 1.3 Login as admin → copy access token to @adminToken below
POST {{base}}/auth/login/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "admin123"
}

###

# ── Paste tokens here after running 1.2 and 1.3 ──
@userToken  = PASTE_USER_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
@adminToken = PASTE_ADMIN_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

### 1.4 Get own profile (authenticated)
GET {{base}}/auth/profile/
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

###

### 1.5 List all users (Admin only)
GET {{base}}/auth/users/
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 1.6 List all users without token → expect 401
GET {{base}}/auth/users/

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 2. TRAINERS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────

### 2.1 List active trainers (public)
GET {{base}}/gym/trainers/

###

### 2.2 Create trainer (Admin only)
POST {{base}}/gym/trainers/
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "first_name": "Иван",
  "last_name": "Петров",
  "email": "ivan.petrov@gym.com",
  "phone": "+7-900-000-0001",
  "specialization": "Йога",
  "bio": "Опытный инструктор по йоге с 10-летним стажем.",
  "is_active": true
}

###

### 2.3 Create trainer without token → expect 403
POST {{base}}/gym/trainers/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "first_name": "Анна",
  "last_name": "Сидорова",
  "email": "anna@gym.com",
  "specialization": "Пилатес"
}

###

### 2.4 Get trainer detail (public) — replace 1 with real id
GET {{base}}/gym/trainers/1/

###

### 2.5 Update trainer (Admin only) — replace 1 with real id
PUT {{base}}/gym/trainers/1/
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "first_name": "Иван",
  "last_name": "Петров",
  "email": "ivan.petrov@gym.com",
  "phone": "+7-900-000-0001",
  "specialization": "Йога и медитация",
  "bio": "Обновлённое описание.",
  "is_active": true
}

###

### 2.6 Soft-delete trainer (Admin only) — replace 1 with real id
DELETE {{base}}/gym/trainers/1/
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 3. SESSIONS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────

### 3.1 List active sessions (public)
GET {{base}}/gym/sessions/

###

### 3.2 Filter sessions by date (public)
GET {{base}}/gym/sessions/?date=2026-04-01

###

### 3.3 Create session (Admin only) — trainer must exist, replace trainer id
POST {{base}}/gym/sessions/
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "title": "Утренняя йога",
  "description": "Занятие для начинающих",
  "trainer": 1,
  "date": "2026-04-01",
  "start_time": "09:00:00",
  "end_time": "10:00:00",
  "capacity": 10,
  "is_active": true
}

###

### 3.4 Create session with invalid time (end <= start) → expect 400
POST {{base}}/gym/sessions/
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "title": "Плохое занятие",
  "trainer": 1,
  "date": "2026-04-01",
  "start_time": "10:00:00",
  "end_time": "09:00:00",
  "capacity": 5
}

###

### 3.5 Get session detail — replace 1 with real id
GET {{base}}/gym/sessions/1/

###

### 3.6 Delete session (cancels all bookings) — replace 1 with real id
DELETE {{base}}/gym/sessions/1/
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 4. BOOKINGS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────

### 4.1 Create booking (authenticated user) — replace session_id
POST {{base}}/gym/bookings/
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

{
  "session_id": 1
}

###

### 4.2 Create booking without token → expect 401
POST {{base}}/gym/bookings/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "session_id": 1
}

###

### 4.3 List own bookings (regular user sees only own)
GET {{base}}/gym/bookings/
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

###

### 4.4 List all bookings (Admin sees all)
GET {{base}}/gym/bookings/
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 4.5 Get booking detail — replace 1 with real id
GET {{base}}/gym/bookings/1/
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

###

### 4.6 Update booking status to cancelled — replace 1 with real id
PUT {{base}}/gym/bookings/1/status/
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

{
  "status": "cancelled"
}

###

### 4.7 Restore booking (cancelled → confirmed) — replace 1 with real id
PUT {{base}}/gym/bookings/1/status/
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

{
  "status": "confirmed"
}

###

### 4.8 Delete (soft-cancel) booking — replace 1 with real id
DELETE {{base}}/gym/bookings/1/
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

###

### 4.9 Get all bookings for a specific user (Admin or self) — replace 1 with user id
GET {{base}}/gym/users/1/bookings/
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 4.10 Duplicate booking → expect 400
POST {{base}}/gym/bookings/
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

{
  "session_id": 1
}

###
